OL,3,C'Progress is being made' in tackling
OL,4,Cracism in football, Premier League CEO
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,FSpeaking to ITV News, Premier League
OL,8,FChief Executive Richard Masters said:
OL,9,F"I don't think any professional
OL,10,Ffootballer from any walk of life
OL,11,Fshould have to face abuse like that."
OL,13,FHe said efforts to stamp it out
OL,14,Fcontinues, but he cited the recently
OL,15,Fimplemented Online Safety Act, and
OL,16,Fwork with social media platforms to
OL,17,Fintroduce new tools to clamp down on
OL,18,Fits proliferation on the internet.
OL,20,FBut he said: "It's not a complete
OL,21,Fpiece of work yet."
